        h2 1. Clean Code
        ul
          li Maintainable
          li Readable
          li Simple
          li Tested

      section
        h3 Why?

      section
        h3 Total cost of owning a mess
        img(src='images/mess.png')

      section
        h3 Attitude

      section
        h2 2. Meaningful Names
        ul
          li Meaningful, intention-revealing, pronounceable
          li Avoid disinformation
          li <b>Nouns</b> for classes, <b>verbs</b> for methods
          li Do not hesitate to rename poor names globally

      section
        p Intention-revealing
        pre
          code.language-javascript.
            self.getThem = function(theList) {
                var list1 = [];
                for (var i = 0; i < theList.length; i++) {
                    if (theList[i] === 4) {
                        list1.push(theList[i]);
                    }
                }
                return list1;
            };
        pre
          code.language-javascript.
            self.getFlaggedCells = function(gameBoard) {
                var flaggedCells = [];
                $.each(gameBoard, function(index, currentCell) {
                    if (currentCell.status === 'FLAGGED') {
                        flaggedCells.push(currentCell);
                    }
                });
                return flaggedCells;
            };

      section
        h2 3. Functions
        p SMALL
        p Blocks & Indenting
        p Do one thing
        p One level of abstraction per function
        p Reads top-to-bottom
        p Switch statements
        p Arguments
        p No side effects
        p Exceptions
        p DRY

      section
        h2 4. Comments
        p At best, a necessary evil
        p Often lie
        p Do not make up for bad code
        p Clear & expressive code with few comments > complex code with many comments

